    <chapter>
      <title>Compiling the ADG library</title>

      <section>
        <title>Requirements</title>
        <para>
        The ADG library is strongly based on the GObject framework (included inside
        the GLib abstraction layer) and uses Cairo as rendering engine. Both the
        libraries are required.
        </para>

        <variablelist>

        <varlistentry>
        <term><ulink url="http://www.gtk.org/">GLib</ulink></term>
        <listitem><para>Required v.2.10 or later</para></listitem>
        </varlistentry>

        <varlistentry>
        <term><ulink url="http://cairographics.org/">Cairo</ulink></term>
        <listitem><para>Required v.1.0 or later</para></listitem>
        </varlistentry>

        </variablelist>

        <para>In order to compile the adg-demo demonstration program, you need also
        the Gtk+-2.0 user interface library.</para>

        <variablelist>

        <varlistentry>
        <term><ulink url="http://www.gtk.org/">Gtk+-2.0</ulink></term>
        <listitem><para>Required v.2.8 or later</para></listitem>
        </varlistentry>

        </variablelist>
      </section>
    </chapter>
